Method Detail

parseHeader

protected static ArrayList<ReceivedCookie> parseHeader(String httpHeader)
                                                throws ParseException
Parses the value of a "Cookie:" HTTP header and returns a list of received cookies which it contained. - A single "Cookie:" header is allowed to contain multiple cookies. Further, a HTTP request can contain multiple "Cookie" keys!.

Parameters:
httpHeader - The value of a "Cookie:" header (i.e. the prefix "Cookie:" must not be contained in this parameter!)
Returns:
A list of ReceivedCookie objects. The validity of their name/value pairs is not deeply checked, their getName() / getValue() might throw!
Throws:
ParseException - If the general formatting of the cookie is wrong.

encodeToHeaderValue

protected String encodeToHeaderValue()
Description copied from class: Cookie
Encodes the content of this cookie to the HTTP header value representation as of RFC2965. The key "set-cookie2:" is not prefixed to the returned String!
